The '''National Center for Culture and Arts''' (NCCA) of [[King Hussein]] Foundation is a non-profit and non-governmental organisation that was established in 1987 by Her Majesty [[Queen Noor of Jordan|Queen Noor Al Hussein]] with the aim of developing understanding and awareness of the value of the arts in the educational process and to promote social development issues through the arts in [[Jordan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The National Centre for Culture & Arts|url=http://www.creativejordan.org/BreedingCreativity/81|publisher=Creative Jordan|accessdate=4 October 2014}}</ref> Headquartered in [[Amman, Jordan]], the NCCA has been at the forefront of the development of theater and dance in Jordan and the region and is known today to be a pioneer educational and cultural institution in the Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jordan National Centre for Culture and Arts to Become a Centre of Excellence on Theatre-Based Peer Education|url=http://arabstates.unfpa.org/public/pid/14628|publisher=UNFPA Arab States|accessdate=4 October 2014|date=9 July 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006085357/http://arabstates.unfpa.org/public/pid/14628|archivedate=6 October 2014|df=}}</ref>

